notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-20T11:01:07.466Z",claude-code-agent,"Implemented (test-only + CI, zero production change). Root cause confirmed: gate scripts are already Windows-correct (static-quality-gate normalizes reported paths via relativeToRepo; docs-skills-gate builds logical paths with path.posix) — only the specs mismatched native vs POSIX separators. Fixes per failure class: (1) static-quality-gate walkFiles/resolveRelativeImport/checkOrphanSourceModules use POSIX-keyed fs mocks against drive-lettered win32 candidates → new harness.mockPosixPath() forces node:path→path.posix in those 3 helper tests (inverse of runtime-schema-path-win32-guard); node:path added to harness builtinUnmocks. (2) docs-skills-gate collectMarkdownFiles readdir mock keyed on /docs → normalize dir separators in the mock. (3) bundle-cli + contracts-snapshot stringContaining path assertions → compare against path.join(...) (native per host). (4) smoke-npx-from-pack execFileSync mocks keyed on bare npm/npx but resolveCommand appends .cmd on win32 → baseCommand() strips .cmd in all mocks. Re-broadened per-PR windows-regression CI job to the full tests/unit/scripts/ directory and locked it in ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts. Verified on Linux: 4774 tests pass, coverage literal 100/100/100/100, quality:static + docs-skills + contracts + security:scan green, isolated temp-dir smoke (init/create/update/list/close/validate) clean. mockPosixPath forces POSIX on every host, so the Linux helper-test run faithfully reproduces the Windows path; the windows-regression job is the final oracle."
