body: "## Context\n\npm-dita's shebang-strip fix took the windows-regression script suite from ~360 SyntaxError failures to **0 SyntaxError** (verified on commit b2e07c05, run 27868024561). The residual ~28 failures across 5 files are a separate, pre-existing class and are intentionally NOT gated by the per-PR `windows-regression` job yet.\n\n## Failing files + root cause (all path-separator / mocked-path)\n\n- `tests/unit/scripts/bundle-cli.spec.ts` (1): asserts `expect.stringContaining(\"dist/cli.js\")`; script builds the path with `path.join` → `dist\\cli.js` on Windows.\n- `tests/unit/scripts/contracts-snapshot.spec.ts` (1): asserts `stringContaining(\"tests/fixtures/contracts/full.json\")`; same native-separator mismatch.\n- `tests/unit/scripts/release/static-quality-gate.spec.ts` (3): `walkFiles` returns `\\root\\a.ts` vs expected `/root/a.ts`; `resolveRelativeImport` returns null because its `existsSync` checks build win32 paths that miss the POSIX-keyed mock; `checkOrphanSourceModules` mis-flags `src/used.ts` for the same reason.\n- `tests/unit/scripts/release/docs-skills-gate.spec.ts` (4): `collectMarkdownFiles` returns backslash paths; link resolution compares POSIX vs native and mis-detects broken links.\n- `tests/unit/scripts/smoke-npx-from-pack.spec.ts` (19): `scripts/smoke-npx-from-pack.mjs:42` throws 'npm pack did not produce a tarball name' — likely `resolveCommand` returning `npm.cmd` on Windows vs the POSIX-keyed `execFileSync` mock.\n\n## Two viable fix strategies\n\n1. **Test-only (lowest risk):** force POSIX path semantics in these unit specs via `vi.doMock(\"node:path\", () => path.posix)` (the inverse of the existing `runtime-schema-path-win32-guard.spec.ts` which forces `path.win32`), and normalize the two `stringContaining` assertions. Zero production change.\n2. **Script-correctness:** normalize internal path comparisons/return values to POSIX in `static-quality-gate.mjs` / `docs-skills-gate.mjs` (no-op on Linux, correct on Windows). Higher value but touches release-critical gates — needs a full coverage + gates run.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] All `tests/unit/scripts/**` specs pass on windows-latest.\n- [ ] Re-broaden the per-PR `windows-regression` job to the full `tests/unit/scripts/` directory and lock it in `ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts`.\n- [ ] Coverage stays 100/100/100/100; release gates (static/docs-skills) still pass on ubuntu.\n- [ ] Also sweep the non-script nightly separator failures (e.g. init-command / schema-command) pm-i84i listed.\n\n## Evidence\n- Green-on-shebang, separator-only run: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/actions/runs/27868024561 (commit b2e07c05)\n- Parent fix: pm-dita; original umbrella: pm-i84i; GH #315"
